<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Damped_harmonic_oscillator">Damped harmonic oscillator</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Harmonic_oscillator&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2" title="Edit section: Damped harmonic oscillator">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<div class="thumb tright"><div class="thumbinner" style="width:202px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Damping_1.svg" class="image"><img alt="" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fd/Damping_1.svg/200px-Damping_1.svg.png" width="200" height="110" class="thumbimage" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fd/Damping_1.svg/300px-Damping_1.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fd/Damping_1.svg/400px-Damping_1.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="650" data-file-height="356"></a>  <div class="thumbcaption"><div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Damping_1.svg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>Dependence of the system behavior on the value of the damping ratio <i>ζ</i></div></div></div>
<div class="thumb tright"><div class="thumbinner" style="width:222px;"><div id="mwe_player_0" class="PopUpMediaTransform" style="width:220px;" videopayload="<div class=&quot;mediaContainer&quot; style=&quot;width:640px&quot;><video id=&quot;mwe_player_1&quot; poster=&quot;//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a5/Oscillatory_motion_acceleration.ogv/640px--Oscillatory_motion_acceleration.ogv.jpg&quot; controls=&quot;&quot; preload=&quot;none&quot; autoplay=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;width:640px;height:480px&quot; class=&quot;kskin&quot; data-durationhint=&quot;27.694333333333&quot; data-startoffset=&quot;0&quot; data-mwtitle=&quot;Oscillatory_motion_acceleration.ogv&quot; data-mwprovider=&quot;wikimediacommons&quot;><source src=&quot;//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/a/a5/Oscillatory_motion_acceleration.ogv&quot; type=&quot;video/ogg; codecs=&amp;quot;theora, vorbis&amp;quot;&quot; data-title=&quot;Original Ogg file, 640 × 480 (1.07 Mbps)&quot; data-shorttitle=&quot;Ogg source&quot; data-width=&quot;640&quot; data-height=&quot;480&quot; data-bandwidth=&quot;1067408&quot; data-framerate=&quot;29.97002997003&quot;/><source src=&quot;//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/transcoded/a/a5/Oscillatory_motion_acceleration.ogv/Oscillatory_motion_acceleration.ogv.480p.webm&quot; type=&quot;video/webm; codecs=&amp;quot;vp8, vorbis&amp;quot;&quot; data-title=&quot;SD WebM (480P)&quot; data-shorttitle=&quot;WebM 480P&quot; data-transcodekey=&quot;480p.webm&quot; data-width=&quot;640&quot; data-height=&quot;480&quot; data-bandwidth=&quot;1118888&quot; data-framerate=&quot;29.97002997003&quot;/><source src=&quot;//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/transcoded/a/a5/Oscillatory_motion_acceleration.ogv/Oscillatory_motion_acceleration.ogv.160p.webm&quot; type=&quot;video/webm; codecs=&amp;quot;vp8, vorbis&amp;quot;&quot; data-title=&quot;Low bandwidth WebM (160P)&quot; data-shorttitle=&quot;WebM 160P&quot; data-transcodekey=&quot;160p.webm&quot; data-width=&quot;214&quot; data-height=&quot;160&quot; data-bandwidth=&quot;225144&quot; data-framerate=&quot;29.97002997003&quot;/><source src=&quot;//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/transcoded/a/a5/Oscillatory_motion_acceleration.ogv/Oscillatory_motion_acceleration.ogv.240p.webm&quot; type=&quot;video/webm; codecs=&amp;quot;vp8, vorbis&amp;quot;&quot; data-title=&quot;Small WebM (240P)&quot; data-shorttitle=&quot;WebM 240P&quot; data-transcodekey=&quot;240p.webm&quot; data-width=&quot;320&quot; data-height=&quot;240&quot; data-bandwidth=&quot;338112&quot; data-framerate=&quot;29.97002997003&quot;/><source src=&quot;//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/transcoded/a/a5/Oscillatory_motion_acceleration.ogv/Oscillatory_motion_acceleration.ogv.360p.webm&quot; type=&quot;video/webm; codecs=&amp;quot;vp8, vorbis&amp;quot;&quot; data-title=&quot;WebM (360P)&quot; data-shorttitle=&quot;WebM 360P&quot; data-transcodekey=&quot;360p.webm&quot; data-width=&quot;480&quot; data-height=&quot;360&quot; data-bandwidth=&quot;597448&quot; data-framerate=&quot;29.97002997003&quot;/></video></div>"><img alt="File:Oscillatory motion acceleration.ogv" style="width:220px;height:165px" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a5/Oscillatory_motion_acceleration.ogv/220px--Oscillatory_motion_acceleration.ogv.jpg"><a href="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/a/a5/Oscillatory_motion_acceleration.ogv" title="Play media" target="new"><span class="play-btn-large"><span class="mw-tmh-playtext">Play media</span></span></a></div>  <div class="thumbcaption"><div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Oscillatory_motion_acceleration.ogv" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>A damped harmonic oscillator, which slows down due to friction</div></div></div>
<div class="thumb tright"><div class="thumbinner" style="width:222px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Guitar_strings.jpg" class="image"><img alt="" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c8/Guitar_strings.jpg/220px-Guitar_strings.jpg" width="220" height="165" class="thumbimage" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c8/Guitar_strings.jpg/330px-Guitar_strings.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c8/Guitar_strings.jpg/440px-Guitar_strings.jpg 2x" data-file-width="2048" data-file-height="1536"></a>  <div class="thumbcaption"><div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Guitar_strings.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>Another damped harmonic oscillator</div></div></div>
<p>In real oscillators, friction, or damping, slows the motion of the system. Due to frictional force, the velocity decreases in proportion to the acting frictional force. While simple harmonic motion oscillates with only the restoring force acting on the system, damped harmonic motion experiences friction. In many vibrating systems the frictional force <i>F</i><sub>f</sub> can be modeled as being proportional to the velocity <i>v</i> of the object: <span class="nowrap"><i>F</i><sub>f</sub> = −<i>cv</i></span>, where <i>c</i> is called the <i>viscous damping coefficient</i>.
</p><p>Balance of forces (<a href="/wiki/Newton%27s_second_law" class="mw-redirect" title="Newton's second law">Newton's second law</a>) for damped harmonic oscillators is then
</p>
<dl><dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle F=F_{\text{ext}}-kx-c{\frac {\mathrm {d} x}{\mathrm {d} t}}=m{\frac {\mathrm {d} ^{2}x}{\mathrm {d} t^{2}}}.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <mi>F</mi>
        <mo>=</mo>
        <msub>
          <mi>F</mi>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mtext>ext</mtext>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo>−<!-- − --></mo>
        <mi>k</mi>
