    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle {\frac {\mathrm {d} ^{2}x}{\mathrm {d} t^{2}}}+2\zeta \omega _{0}{\frac {\mathrm {d} x}{\mathrm {d} t}}+\omega _{0}^{\,2}x=0,}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/18bbe1985f7985ad74b1b34260ee862090284ce1" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.171ex; width:27.534ex; height:6.009ex;" alt="{\frac {\mathrm {d} ^{2}x}{\mathrm {d} t^{2}}}+2\zeta \omega _{0}{\frac {\mathrm {d} x}{\mathrm {d} t}}+\omega _{0}^{\,2}x=0,"></span></dd></dl>
<p>where
</p>
<dl><dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle \omega _{0}={\sqrt {\frac {k}{m}}}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <msub>
          <mi>ω<!-- ω --></mi>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mn>0</mn>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo>=</mo>
        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <msqrt>
            <mfrac>
              <mi>k</mi>
              <mi>m</mi>
            </mfrac>
          </msqrt>
        </mrow>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \omega _{0}={\sqrt {\frac {k}{m}}}}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/4949e44f7e8b28b77faafce9c399525330d391d5" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.338ex; width:10.799ex; height:6.176ex;" alt="{\displaystyle \omega _{0}={\sqrt {\frac {k}{m}}}}"></span> is called the 'undamped <a href="/wiki/Angular_frequency" title="Angular frequency">angular frequency</a> of the oscillator' and</dd></dl>
<dl><dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle \zeta ={\frac {c}{2{\sqrt {mk}}}}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <mi>ζ<!-- ζ --></mi>
        <mo>=</mo>
        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mi>c</mi>
            <mrow>
              <mn>2</mn>
              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                <msqrt>
                  <mi>m</mi>
                  <mi>k</mi>
                </msqrt>
              </mrow>
            </mrow>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \zeta ={\frac {c}{2{\sqrt {mk}}}}}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/7b5cba92dfb2c3942fb2b9446f3966d0f90f44db" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.838ex; width:11.38ex; height:5.676ex;" alt="{\displaystyle \zeta ={\frac {c}{2{\sqrt {mk}}}}}"></span> is called the 'damping ratio'.</dd></dl>
<div class="thumb tright"><div class="thumbinner" style="width:202px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Step_response_for_two-pole_feedback_amplifier.PNG" class="image"><img alt="" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4f/Step_response_for_two-pole_feedback_amplifier.PNG/200px-Step_response_for_two-pole_feedback_amplifier.PNG" width="200" height="213" class="thumbimage" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4f/Step_response_for_two-pole_feedback_amplifier.PNG/300px-Step_response_for_two-pole_feedback_amplifier.PNG 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4f/Step_response_for_two-pole_feedback_amplifier.PNG/400px-Step_response_for_two-pole_feedback_amplifier.PNG 2x" data-file-width="465" data-file-height="496"></a>  <div class="thumbcaption"><div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Step_response_for_two-pole_feedback_amplifier.PNG" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>Step-response of a damped harmonic oscillator; curves are plotted for three values of <span class="nowrap"><i>μ</i> = <i>ω</i><sub>1</sub> = <i>ω</i><sub>0</sub><span class="nowrap">√<span style="border-top:1px solid; padding:0 0.1em;">1&nbsp;−&nbsp;<i>ζ</i><sup>2</sup></span></span></span>. Time is in units of the decay time <span class="nowrap"><i>τ</i> = 1/(<i>ζω</i><sub>0</sub>)</span>.</div></div></div>
<p>The value of the damping ratio <i>ζ</i> critically determines the behavior of the system. A damped harmonic oscillator can be:
</p>
<ul><li><i>Overdamped</i> (<i>ζ</i> &gt; 1): The system returns (<a href="/wiki/Exponential_decay" title="Exponential decay">exponentially decays</a>) to steady state without oscillating.  Larger values of the damping ratio <i>ζ</i> return to equilibrium more slowly.</li>
<li><i>Critically damped</i> (<i>ζ</i> = 1):  The system returns to steady state as quickly as possible without oscillating (although overshoot can occur).  This is often desired for the damping of systems such as doors.</li>
<li><i>Underdamped</i> (<i>ζ</i> &lt; 1): The system oscillates (with a slightly different frequency than the undamped case) with the amplitude gradually decreasing to zero. The <a href="/wiki/Angular_frequency" title="Angular frequency">angular frequency</a> of the underdamped harmonic oscillator is given by <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle \omega _{1}=\omega _{0}{\sqrt {1-\zeta ^{2}}},}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <msub>
          <mi>ω<!-- ω --></mi>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mn>1</mn>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo>=</mo>
        <msub>
          <mi>ω<!-- ω --></mi>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mn>0</mn>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <msqrt>
            <mn>1</mn>
            <mo>−<!-- − --></mo>
            <msup>
              <mi>ζ<!-- ζ --></mi>
              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                <mn>2</mn>
              </mrow>
            </msup>
          </msqrt>
        </mrow>
        <mo>,</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \omega _{1}=\omega _{0}{\sqrt {1-\zeta ^{2}}},}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/a5b8bc854ac871992ff69e8d387ac15335bb18bb" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -1.671ex; width:17.244ex; height:4.843ex;" alt="\omega _{1}=\omega _{0}{\sqrt {1-\zeta ^{2}}},"></span> the <a href="/wiki/Exponential_decay" title="Exponential decay">exponential decay</a> of the underdamped harmonic oscillator is given by <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle \lambda =\omega _{0}\zeta .}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <mi>λ<!-- λ --></mi>
        <mo>=</mo>
        <msub>
          <mi>ω<!-- ω --></mi>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mn>0</mn>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mi>ζ<!-- ζ --></mi>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \lambda =\omega _{0}\zeta .}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/a2926824efa32307d913c22dc481d695cdef9e11" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:8.696ex; height:2.509ex;" alt="\lambda =\omega _{0}\zeta ."></span></li></ul>
<p>The <a href="/wiki/Q_factor" title="Q factor">Q factor</a> of a damped oscillator is defined as
</p>
<dl><dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle Q=2\pi \times {\frac {\text{energy stored}}{\text{energy lost per cycle}}}.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <mi>Q</mi>
        <mo>=</mo>
        <mn>2</mn>
        <mi>π<!-- π --></mi>
        <mo>×<!-- × --></mo>
        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mtext>energy stored</mtext>
            <mtext>energy lost per cycle</mtext>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle Q=2\pi \times {\frac {\text{energy stored}}{\text{energy lost per cycle}}}.}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/59dd5a5527e2f6216bc27562a72e50ddf90df2de" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.338ex; width:31.994ex; height:5.843ex;" alt="{\displaystyle Q=2\pi \times {\frac {\text{energy stored}}{\text{energy lost per cycle}}}.}"></span></dd></dl>
<p><i>Q</i> is related to the damping ratio by the equation <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle Q={\frac {1}{2\zeta }}.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <mi>Q</mi>
        <mo>=</mo>
        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mn>1</mn>
            <mrow>
              <mn>2</mn>
              <mi>ζ<!-- ζ --></mi>
            </mrow>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle Q={\frac {1}{2\zeta }}.}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/39aaad7ad414bf791e30897344597225b2ef4a16" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.338ex; width:8.677ex; height:5.676ex;" alt="{\displaystyle Q={\frac {1}{2\zeta }}.}"></span>
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Driven_harmonic_oscillators">Driven harmonic oscillators</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Harmonic_oscillator&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3" title="Edit section: Driven harmonic oscillators">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<p>Driven harmonic oscillators are damped oscillators further affected by an externally applied force <i>F</i>(<i>t</i>).
</p><p><a href="/wiki/Newton%27s_second_law" class="mw-redirect" title="Newton's second law">Newton's second law</a> takes the form
</p>
<dl><dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle F(t)-kx-c{\frac {\mathrm {d} x}{\mathrm {d} t}}=m{\frac {\mathrm {d} ^{2}x}{\mathrm {d} t^{2}}}.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <mi>F</mi>
        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
        <mi>t</mi>
        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
        <mo>−<!-- − --></mo>
        <mi>k</mi>
        <mi>x</mi>
        <mo>−<!-- − --></mo>
        <mi>c</mi>
        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mrow>
              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                <mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi>
              </mrow>
              <mi>x</mi>
            </mrow>
            <mrow>
              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                <mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi>
              </mrow>
              <mi>t</mi>
            </mrow>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=</mo>
        <mi>m</mi>
        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mrow>
              <msup>
                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                  <mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi>
                </mrow>
                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                  <mn>2</mn>
                </mrow>
              </msup>
              <mi>x</mi>
            </mrow>
            <mrow>
              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                <mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi>
              </mrow>
              <msup>
                <mi>t</mi>
                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                  <mn>2</mn>
                </mrow>
              </msup>
            </mrow>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle F(t)-kx-c{\frac {\mathrm {d} x}{\mathrm {d} t}}=m{\frac {\mathrm {d} ^{2}x}{\mathrm {d} t^{2}}}.}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/794547ed5f938a625560845f14862c7bd5fbf745" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.171ex; width:27.375ex; height:6.009ex;" alt="F(t)-kx-c{\frac {\mathrm {d} x}{\mathrm {d} t}}=m{\frac {\mathrm {d} ^{2}x}{\mathrm {d} t^{2}}}."></span></dd></dl>
<p>It is usually rewritten into the form
</p>
<dl><dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle {\frac {\mathrm {d} ^{2}x}{\mathrm {d} t^{2}}}+2\zeta \omega _{0}{\frac {\mathrm {d} x}{\mathrm {d} t}}+\omega _{0}^{2}x={\frac {F(t)}{m}}.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mrow>
              <msup>
                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                  <mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi>
                </mrow>
                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                  <mn>2</mn>
                </mrow>
              </msup>
              <mi>x</mi>
            </mrow>
            <mrow>
              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                <mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi>
              </mrow>
              <msup>
                <mi>t</mi>
                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                  <mn>2</mn>
                </mrow>
              </msup>
            </mrow>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>+</mo>
        <mn>2</mn>
        <mi>ζ<!-- ζ --></mi>
        <msub>
          <mi>ω<!-- ω --></mi>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mn>0</mn>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mrow>
              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                <mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi>
              </mrow>
              <mi>x</mi>
            </mrow>
            <mrow>
              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                <mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi>
              </mrow>
              <mi>t</mi>
            </mrow>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>+</mo>
        <msubsup>
          <mi>ω<!-- ω --></mi>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mn>0</mn>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mn>2</mn>
          </mrow>
        </msubsup>
        <mi>x</mi>
        <mo>=</mo>
        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mrow>
              <mi>F</mi>
              <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
              <mi>t</mi>
              <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
            </mrow>
            <mi>m</mi>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle {\frac {\mathrm {d} ^{2}x}{\mathrm {d} t^{2}}}+2\zeta \omega _{0}{\frac {\mathrm {d} x}{\mathrm {d} t}}+\omega _{0}^{2}x={\frac {F(t)}{m}}.}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/61e55619b011f1893671806f3df229287dbc5333" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.171ex; width:31.21ex; height:6.009ex;" alt="{\frac {\mathrm {d} ^{2}x}{\mathrm {d} t^{2}}}+2\zeta \omega _{0}{\frac {\mathrm {d} x}{\mathrm {d} t}}+\omega _{0}^{2}x={\frac {F(t)}{m}}."></span></dd></dl>
<p>This equation can be solved exactly for any driving force, using the solutions <i>z</i>(<i>t</i>) which satisfy the unforced equation:
</p>
<dl><dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle {\frac {\mathrm {d} ^{2}z}{\mathrm {d} t^{2}}}+2\zeta \omega _{0}{\frac {\mathrm {d} z}{\mathrm {d} t}}+\omega _{0}^{2}z=0,}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mrow>
              <msup>
                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                  <mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi>
                </mrow>
                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                  <mn>2</mn>
                </mrow>
              </msup>
              <mi>z</mi>
            </mrow>
            <mrow>
              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                <mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi>
              </mrow>
              <msup>
                <mi>t</mi>
                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                  <mn>2</mn>
                </mrow>
              </msup>
            </mrow>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>+</mo>
        <mn>2</mn>
        <mi>ζ<!-- ζ --></mi>
        <msub>
          <mi>ω<!-- ω --></mi>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mn>0</mn>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mrow>
              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                <mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi>
              </mrow>
              <mi>z</mi>
            </mrow>
            <mrow>
              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                <mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi>
              </mrow>
              <mi>t</mi>
            </mrow>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>+</mo>
        <msubsup>
          <mi>ω<!-- ω --></mi>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mn>0</mn>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mn>2</mn>
          </mrow>
        </msubsup>
        <mi>z</mi>
        <mo>=</mo>
        <mn>0</mn>
        <mo>,</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle {\frac {\mathrm {d} ^{2}z}{\mathrm {d} t^{2}}}+2\zeta \omega _{0}{\frac {\mathrm {d} z}{\mathrm {d} t}}+\omega _{0}^{2}z=0,}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/150594f17c0298d287b4016de14c02553047b27a" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.171ex; width:26.422ex; height:6.009ex;" alt="{\frac {\mathrm {d} ^{2}z}{\mathrm {d} t^{2}}}+2\zeta \omega _{0}{\frac {\mathrm {d} z}{\mathrm {d} t}}+\omega _{0}^{2}z=0,"></span></dd></dl>
<p>and which can be expressed as damped sinusoidal oscillations,
</p>
<dl><dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle z(t)=A\mathrm {e} ^{-\zeta \omega _{0}t}\ \sin \left({\sqrt {1-\zeta ^{2}}}\ \omega _{0}t+\varphi \right),}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <mi>z</mi>
        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
        <mi>t</mi>
        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
        <mo>=</mo>
        <mi>A</mi>
        <msup>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi mathvariant="normal">e</mi>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mo>−<!-- − --></mo>
            <mi>ζ<!-- ζ --></mi>
            <msub>
              <mi>ω<!-- ω --></mi>
              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                <mn>0</mn>
              </mrow>
            </msub>
            <mi>t</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
        <mtext>&nbsp;</mtext>
        <mi>sin</mi>
        <mo>⁡<!-- ⁡ --></mo>
        <mrow>
          <mo>(</mo>
          <mrow>
            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
              <msqrt>
                <mn>1</mn>
                <mo>−<!-- − --></mo>
                <msup>
                  <mi>ζ<!-- ζ --></mi>
                  <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                    <mn>2</mn>
                  </mrow>
                </msup>
              </msqrt>
            </mrow>
            <mtext>&nbsp;</mtext>
            <msub>
              <mi>ω<!-- ω --></mi>
              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                <mn>0</mn>
              </mrow>
            </msub>
            <mi>t</mi>
            <mo>+</mo>
            <mi>φ<!-- φ --></mi>
          </mrow>
          <mo>)</mo>
        </mrow>
        <mo>,</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle z(t)=A\mathrm {e} ^{-\zeta \omega _{0}t}\ \sin \left({\sqrt {1-\zeta ^{2}}}\ \omega _{0}t+\varphi \right),}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/a5ff5591ceeb94d8c65921eead1b32d8df98a34e" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.505ex; width:39.015ex; height:6.176ex;" alt="{\displaystyle z(t)=A\mathrm {e} ^{-\zeta \omega _{0}t}\ \sin \left({\sqrt {1-\zeta ^{2}}}\ \omega _{0}t+\varphi \right),}"></span></dd></dl>
<p>in the case where <i>ζ</i>&nbsp;≤&nbsp;1. The amplitude <i>A</i> and phase <i>φ</i> determine the behavior needed to match the initial conditions.
</p>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Step_input">Step input</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Harmonic_oscillator&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4" title="Edit section: Step input">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable">See also: <a href="/wiki/Step_response" title="Step response">Step response</a></div>
<p>In the case <i>ζ</i>&nbsp;&lt;&nbsp;1 and a unit step input with&nbsp;<i>x</i>(0)&nbsp;=&nbsp;0:
</p>
<dl><dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle {F(t) \over m}={\begin{cases}\omega _{0}^{2}&amp;t\geq 0\\0&amp;t<0\end{cases}}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mrow>
