    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \,\!F_{0}}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/2397151c8daede90f8643fd5075254b16f360e6b" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:2.549ex; height:2.509ex;" alt="\,\!F_{0}"></span> is the driving amplitude and <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle \,\!\omega }">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <mspace width="thinmathspace"></mspace>
        <mspace width="negativethinmathspace"></mspace>
        <mi>ω<!-- ω --></mi>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \,\!\omega }</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/027914d0c9304eee91bd432c37c050be3aa197a9" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.446ex; height:1.676ex;" alt="\,\!\omega "></span> is the driving <a href="/wiki/Frequency" title="Frequency">frequency</a> for a sinusoidal driving mechanism. This type of system appears in <a href="/wiki/Alternating_current" title="Alternating current">AC</a> driven <a href="/wiki/RLC_circuit" title="RLC circuit">RLC circuits</a> (<a href="/wiki/Electrical_resistance" class="mw-redirect" title="Electrical resistance">resistor</a>-<a href="/wiki/Inductor" title="Inductor">inductor</a>-<a href="/wiki/Capacitor" title="Capacitor">capacitor</a>) and driven spring systems having internal mechanical resistance or external <a href="/wiki/Air_resistance" class="mw-redirect" title="Air resistance">air resistance</a>.
</p><p>The general solution is a sum of a <a href="/wiki/Transient_(oscillation)" title="Transient (oscillation)">transient</a> solution that depends on initial conditions, and a <a href="/wiki/Steady_state" title="Steady state">steady state</a> that is independent of initial conditions and depends only on the driving amplitude <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle \,\!F_{0}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <mspace width="thinmathspace"></mspace>
        <mspace width="negativethinmathspace"></mspace>
        <msub>
          <mi>F</mi>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mn>0</mn>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \,\!F_{0}}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/2397151c8daede90f8643fd5075254b16f360e6b" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:2.549ex; height:2.509ex;" alt="\,\!F_{0}"></span>, driving frequency, <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle \,\!\omega }">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <mspace width="thinmathspace"></mspace>
        <mspace width="negativethinmathspace"></mspace>
        <mi>ω<!-- ω --></mi>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \,\!\omega }</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/027914d0c9304eee91bd432c37c050be3aa197a9" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.446ex; height:1.676ex;" alt="\,\!\omega "></span>, undamped angular frequency <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle \,\!\omega _{0}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <mspace width="thinmathspace"></mspace>
        <mspace width="negativethinmathspace"></mspace>
        <msub>
          <mi>ω<!-- ω --></mi>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mn>0</mn>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \,\!\omega _{0}}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/aa7ac64547bb29e55a712c094e935636b25f5098" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:2.5ex; height:2.009ex;" alt="\,\!\omega _{0}"></span>, and the damping ratio <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle \,\!\zeta }">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <mspace width="thinmathspace"></mspace>
        <mspace width="negativethinmathspace"></mspace>
        <mi>ζ<!-- ζ --></mi>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \,\!\zeta }</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/ced1b102b15feb5e2a6a55cafc82d718dc025dba" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:1.095ex; height:2.509ex;" alt="\,\!\zeta "></span>.
</p><p>The steady-state solution is proportional to the driving force with an induced phase change of <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle \,\!\varphi }">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <mspace width="thinmathspace"></mspace>
        <mspace width="negativethinmathspace"></mspace>
        <mi>φ<!-- φ --></mi>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \,\!\varphi }</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/ae712e9260150a2eb40842122b81fb726ebee851" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:1.52ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="{\displaystyle \,\!\varphi }"></span>:
</p>
<dl><dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle x(t)={\frac {F_{0}}{mZ_{m}\omega }}\sin(\omega t+\varphi )}">
