            </mfrac>
          </mrow>
          <mo>)</mo>
        </mrow>
        <mo>+</mo>
        <mi>n</mi>
        <mi>π<!-- π --></mi>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \varphi =\arctan \left({\frac {2\omega \omega _{0}\zeta }{\omega ^{2}-\omega _{0}^{2}}}\right)+n\pi }</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/a9bb9a1ff792515288b8b57664b106f93f4cda57" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -3.171ex; width:29.01ex; height:7.509ex;" alt="{\displaystyle \varphi =\arctan \left({\frac {2\omega \omega _{0}\zeta }{\omega ^{2}-\omega _{0}^{2}}}\right)+n\pi }"></span></dd></dl>
<p>is the <a href="/wiki/Phase_(waves)" title="Phase (waves)">phase</a> of the oscillation relative to the driving force. The phase value is usually taken to be between -180 degrees and 0 (that is, it represents a phase lag, for both positive and negative values of the arctan's argument).
</p><p>For a particular driving frequency called the <a href="/wiki/Resonance" title="Resonance">resonance</a>, or resonant frequency <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle \,\!\omega _{r}=\omega _{0}{\sqrt {1-2\zeta ^{2}}}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <mspace width="thinmathspace"></mspace>
        <mspace width="negativethinmathspace"></mspace>
        <msub>
          <mi>ω<!-- ω --></mi>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>r</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo>=</mo>
        <msub>
          <mi>ω<!-- ω --></mi>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
