<p>The transient solution is independent of the forcing function.
</p>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Steady-state_solution">Steady-state solution</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Harmonic_oscillator&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9" title="Edit section: Steady-state solution">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<p>Apply the "<a href="/wiki/Complex_analysis" title="Complex analysis">complex variables</a> method" by solving the auxiliary equation below and then finding the real part of its solution:
</p>
<dl><dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle {\frac {\mathrm {d} ^{2}q}{\mathrm {d} \tau ^{2}}}+2\zeta {\frac {\mathrm {d} q}{\mathrm {d} \tau }}+q=\cos(\omega \tau )+\mathrm {i} \sin(\omega \tau )=\mathrm {e} ^{\mathrm {i} \omega \tau }.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mrow>
              <msup>
                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
