              <mi mathvariant="normal">i</mi>
            </mrow>
            <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
            <mi>ω<!-- ω --></mi>
            <mi>τ<!-- τ --></mi>
            <mo>+</mo>
            <mi>φ<!-- φ --></mi>
            <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle q_{s}=A\mathrm {e} ^{\mathrm {i} (\omega \tau +\varphi )},\ {\frac {\mathrm {d} q_{s}}{\mathrm {d} \tau }}=\mathrm {i} \omega A\mathrm {e} ^{\mathrm {i} (\omega \tau +\varphi )},\ {\frac {\mathrm {d} ^{2}q_{s}}{\mathrm {d} \tau ^{2}}}=-\omega ^{2}A\mathrm {e} ^{\mathrm {i} (\omega \tau +\varphi )}.}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/10462584e5a1b856c9383abb14daecb252b8621c" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.171ex; width:57.915ex; height:6.176ex;" alt="{\displaystyle q_{s}=A\mathrm {e} ^{\mathrm {i} (\omega \tau +\varphi )},\ {\frac {\mathrm {d} q_{s}}{\mathrm {d} \tau }}=\mathrm {i} \omega A\mathrm {e} ^{\mathrm {i} (\omega \tau +\varphi )},\ {\frac {\mathrm {d} ^{2}q_{s}}{\mathrm {d} \tau ^{2}}}=-\omega ^{2}A\mathrm {e} ^{\mathrm {i} (\omega \tau +\varphi )}.}"></span></dd></dl>
<p>Substituting these quantities into the differential equation gives
</p>
<dl><dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle \,\!-\omega ^{2}A\mathrm {e} ^{\mathrm {i} (\omega \tau +\varphi )}+2\zeta \mathrm {i} \omega A\mathrm {e} ^{\mathrm {i} (\omega \tau +\varphi )}+A\mathrm {e} ^{\mathrm {i} (\omega \tau +\varphi )}=(-\omega ^{2}A+2\zeta \mathrm {i} \omega A+A)\mathrm {e} ^{\mathrm {i} (\omega \tau +\varphi )}=\mathrm {e} ^{\mathrm {i} \omega \tau }.}">
