<p>Dividing by the exponential term on the left results in
</p>
<dl><dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle \,\!-\omega ^{2}A+2\zeta \mathrm {i} \omega A+A=\mathrm {e} ^{-\mathrm {i} \varphi }=\cos \varphi -\mathrm {i} \sin \varphi .}">
