  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/03f8ae9c639629827d98a3238344e81addbaa545" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:44.143ex; height:3.176ex;" alt="{\displaystyle \,\!-\omega ^{2}A+2\zeta \mathrm {i} \omega A+A=\mathrm {e} ^{-\mathrm {i} \varphi }=\cos \varphi -\mathrm {i} \sin \varphi .}"></span></dd></dl>
<p>Equating the real and imaginary parts results in two independent equations
</p>
<dl><dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle A(1-\omega ^{2})=\cos \varphi \qquad 2\zeta \omega A=-\sin \varphi .}">
