          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mn>0</mn>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo>=</mo>
        <mn>2</mn>
        <mi>π<!-- π --></mi>
        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <msqrt>
            <mfrac>
              <mi>ℓ<!-- ℓ --></mi>
              <mi>g</mi>
            </mfrac>
          </msqrt>
        </mrow>
        <mo>,</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle T_{0}=2\pi {\sqrt {\frac {\ell }{g}}},}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/1e29d67922dc4389a848ba357c2954f482187071" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -3.171ex; width:12.927ex; height:7.509ex;" alt="T_{0}=2\pi {\sqrt {\frac {\ell }{g}}},"></span></dd></dl>
<p>which is a good approximation of the actual period when <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle \theta _{0}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
